When a civilization relies solely on a single cash crop, its economy becomes vulnerable. A sudden blight or change in global trade could therefore cause widespread famine.
Diversifying investment portfolios mitigates financial risk. When one sector declines, others may compensate, providing greater stability and better long-term returns.
Changes in local zoning laws permitted mixed-use development downtown. This revitalization attracted new businesses, which consequently increased pedestrian traffic and local revenue streams.
